                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Meyer</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-04-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Meyer states that he has been assured by M. Witte that there will not be any
                    disturbances, and that the minister of the interior sent out a circular to all
                    the governors saying that they must hold the police responsible, and that this
                    has reassured the chairman of the Jewish committee. Mr. Meyer says that he
                    thinks that disturbances will occur in isloated places on account of the ill
                    feeling of some subordinates.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
